WEBVTT



00:00:06.304 --> 00:00:10.816
You're listening to Perdido Bay Methodist Church's podcast on the Gospel of Matthew.

00:00:11.296 --> 00:00:13.824
Today's Wednesday, February 11th.

00:00:14.176 --> 00:00:18.784
And today we're reading Matthew chapter 13, verses 1 through 23.

00:00:19.008 --> 00:00:20.768
My name is Scott Hone.

00:00:20.608 --> 00:00:23.488
And this podcast is produced by Kenny Stewart.

00:00:23.904 --> 00:00:25.664
1998, 1999,

00:00:25.504 --> 00:00:29.600
is the third sermon that Matthew records Jesus'

00:00:29.408 --> 00:00:31.680
preaching in the Gospel of Matthew.

00:00:32.032 --> 00:00:33.856
The first sermon

00:00:33.760 --> 00:00:38.368
is the Sermon on the Mount that was chapters five through seven of Matthew

00:00:38.144 --> 00:00:47.872
And then the second sermon, that's the instructions that Jesus gives to the twelve before sending them out of missions. That was Matthew chapter 10.

00:00:48.480 --> 00:00:52.160
Today we're reading the beginning of Jesus' third sermon.

00:00:52.448 --> 00:00:53.280
And,

00:00:53.632 --> 00:01:01.088
Jesus's third sermon is when he uses parables to describe the nature of the kingdom of heaven.

00:01:01.376 --> 00:01:05.792
All the parables in chapter 13 tell us what the kingdom of heaven is like.

00:01:05.472 --> 00:01:09.120
In chapter 13, Jesus tells us eight parables.

00:01:08.960 --> 00:01:14.912
To describe the kingdom of heaven, and he also explains the meaning of two of these parables.

00:01:15.584 --> 00:01:20.000
they came to heaven that's God's rule God's reign

00:01:20.096 --> 00:01:28.608
The kingdom happens whenever God manifests God's authority and power. Why does it look like when God shows us that God is in charge?

00:01:28.672 --> 00:01:32.352
That God is king. See, that's the kingdom of heaven.

00:01:32.672 --> 00:01:36.992
And Jesus uses parables, tells us parables to make

00:01:36.864 --> 00:01:40.384
a comparison to what God's kingdom is like.

00:01:40.160 --> 00:01:44.288
So that we will recognize how God works in the world.

00:01:44.960 --> 00:01:50.368
And Jesus begins his sermon on parables by telling us the parable of the sower.

00:01:50.368 --> 00:01:55.392
A farmer goes out and sows seeds, and actually this farmer is, you know,

00:01:55.200 --> 00:02:02.080
Very generous, even reckless in how he scatters the seed because he throws the seed all over the place.

00:02:01.888 --> 00:02:04.608
Some seed fall on a path.

00:02:04.416 --> 00:02:06.368
And birds come and eat it up.

00:02:06.368 --> 00:02:11.392
And some see they fall on rocky ground and sprout up quickly.

00:02:11.264 --> 00:02:18.944
But then the plants wither when the sun begins to shine. it gets hot because the soil was shallow and it had no root.

00:02:19.296 --> 00:02:27.488
Still other seeds fell among thorns, who choked the seeds out when they started coming to life, and and still other seeds,

00:02:27.360 --> 00:02:29.184
Fell on good soil,

00:02:29.056 --> 00:02:30.528
And they grew.

00:02:30.336 --> 00:02:31.328
Some,

00:02:31.232 --> 00:02:35.232
A hundredfold, sub sixty others, thirtyfold.

00:02:36.512 --> 00:02:41.952
When you read Matthew 13:1-23, you'll notice that Jesus

00:02:41.888 --> 00:02:51.936
Interpose this parable for his disciples. He tells them what the different types of sorrow mean. Jesus says, I'm reading from verse 19 and following. Jesus says, when

00:02:51.456 --> 00:02:56.224
When anyone hears the word of the kingdom and does not understand it,

00:02:56.064 --> 00:02:59.936
"'The evil one comes and snatches away what is sown in the heart.'"

00:03:00.160 --> 00:03:02.944
That is what was sown on the path.

00:03:03.328 --> 00:03:10.112
As for what was sown on rocky ground, this is the one who hears the word and immediately receives it with joy.

00:03:10.176 --> 00:03:14.336
Yet such a person has no root, but endures only for a while.

00:03:14.240 --> 00:03:18.016
And when trouble or persecution arises on account of the word,

00:03:17.856 --> 00:03:20.448
That person immediately falls away.

00:03:20.992 --> 00:03:25.504
As for what was sown among thorns, this is the one who hears the word.

00:03:25.536 --> 00:03:27.840
But the cares of this age,

00:03:27.680 --> 00:03:29.376
The law of wealth

00:03:29.184 --> 00:03:32.448
Choke the word and it heals nothing.

00:03:33.152 --> 00:03:35.840
But as for what, Osona,, good soul,

00:03:35.712 --> 00:03:39.072
This is the one who hears the word and understands it.

00:03:38.816 --> 00:03:43.136
Who indeed bears fruit and yields, in one case, a hundredfold.

00:03:42.880 --> 00:03:46.048
And another sixty, and then another thirty.

00:03:47.840 --> 00:03:50.752
And I'll be honest with you, we can get discouraged.

00:03:51.104 --> 00:03:54.816
When some people don't respond to God's word and God's grace

00:03:55.232 --> 00:03:59.296
Jesus understands that there are some people who won't respond

00:03:59.360 --> 00:04:02.432
And here Jesus explains why that is.

00:04:02.688 --> 00:04:12.736
You know, Jesus also sees that others do respond to God's word and grace. People do hear the word and understand it and are transformed by God's grace. And they end up

00:04:12.256 --> 00:04:15.520
They end up bearing fruit that's amazing and abundant.

00:04:16.032 --> 00:04:19.616
In Jesus's day, a 30-fold harvest was great.

00:04:19.616 --> 00:04:24.224
A 60-volt harvest would have been unimaginably great, grand, amazing.

00:04:24.256 --> 00:04:26.304
But a hundredfold harvest

00:04:26.304 --> 00:04:28.864
That was in the realm of the miraculous.

00:04:29.024 --> 00:04:33.632
And Jesus' point here is that people are responding to God's word.

00:04:33.984 --> 00:04:35.264
You just have to look.

00:04:35.904 --> 00:04:39.840
To where they're responding you just have to look to those who are responding

00:04:39.936 --> 00:04:41.952
Instead of getting distracted

00:04:42.464 --> 00:04:44.800
By those who don't respond.

00:04:46.528 --> 00:04:50.272
I'm going to close with a prayer from the Presbyterian Book of Worship.

00:04:50.592 --> 00:04:52.000
And let us pray.

00:04:52.992 --> 00:04:54.528
Almighty God.

00:04:54.688 --> 00:04:58.016
We thank you for planting in us the seed of your work.

00:04:58.560 --> 00:05:01.856
By your Holy Spirit, help us to receive it with joy, joy,

00:05:01.664 --> 00:05:03.648
And live according to it

00:05:03.776 --> 00:05:07.168
That we may grow in faith and hope and love.

00:05:07.712 --> 00:05:12.992
Through Jesus Christ, our Lord, who lives and reigns with you in the unity of the Holy Spirit, amen.

00:05:14.368 --> 00:05:15.168
Amen.
